\f0\b\fs72 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs62 \cf2 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Butter a 9 by 14 by 2-inch oval {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookware-and-bakeware-materials/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 baking dish}}.\
Peel, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/core/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 core}}, and cut the apples into large wedges. Combine the apples with the zests, juices, sugar, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/spices/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 spices}}. Pour into the dish.\
To make the topping, combine the flour, sugars, salt, oatmeal, and cold butter in the bowl of an electric {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 mixer}} fitted with the paddle attachment. Mix on low speed until the mixture is crumbly and the butter is the size of peas. Scatter evenly over the apples.\
Place the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 crisp}} on a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sheet-pan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 sheet pan}} and bake for 1 hour until the top is brown and the apples are bubbly. Serve warm.\
